data.name: environment.ToolTip
data.value: A list of environment variables to be merged with system environment before launching the executable. The syntax is: KEY1=VAL1 KEY2=VAL2 It is also possible to supply current variables (%VAR%) and extend them, for example: PATH=%PATH%;extension Appends the string "extension" to the current PATH variable.

data.name: working_directory.ToolTip
data.value: Current working directory of the executable being monitored. This value is auto-filled when you change the path to a new executable. The auto-filled value is the directory where the new executable is located.

data.name: assume_crash_if_not_responsive.ToolTip
data.value: Periodically check for responsiveness of the executable's main window and restart it if not responsive. NOTE: When an executable becomes unresponsive, it causes Phoenix itself to be unresponsive for a short amount of time.

data.name: remote_directory.ToolTip
data.value: Remote directory on the SSH server where updated application is located NOTE: there is a deffierence between /some/path and /some/path/ in this field! NOTE: a trailing slash is probably what you want in this field!

data.name: email_body.Text
data.value:
Helios Phoenix crash report,
Instance of #MACHINE_IDENTITY# has encountered a crash. Attached are a screenshot of this machine at the time of crash and optionally a log file (if specified before). This machine is set to fetch updates from #RSYNC_ADDRESS# and obtain commands from #MQTT_ADDRESS#.
This is an automated message, please do not responed.
